We say that the stationary curve  is also nondegenerate respect to the potential a(x), if the bounded kernel of Ja, is the trivial one. The nondegeneracy condition basically implies that Ja, has an appropriate right inverse, so that the curve is isolated in a properly chosen topology. Next, we proceed to state the main result. Theorem 1. Assume that a(x) is a smooth potential and let  be a smooth stationary and nondegenerate curve respect to the length functional  a(x)dr. Assume also that conditions (1.11)-(1.14) are satisfied. Then for any  > 0 small enough, there exists a smooth bounded solution u to the inhomogeneous Allen-Cahn equation (1.10), such that u (x) = w where the function h satisfies h
